/**
30 
 * <p>Operates on classes without using reflection.</p>
31 
 *
32 
 * <p>This class handles invalid <code>null</code> inputs as best it can.
33 
 * Each method documents its behaviour in more detail.</p>
34 
 *
35 
 * <p>The notion of a <code>canonical name</code> includes the human
36 
 * readable name for the type, for example <code>int[]</code>. The
37 
 * non-canonical method variants work with the JVM names, such as
38 
 * <code>[I</code>. </p>
39 
 *
40 
 * @author Apache Software Foundation
41 
 * @author Gary Gregory
42 
 * @author Norm Deane
43 
 * @author Alban Peignier
44 
 * @author Tomasz Blachowicz
45 
 * @since 2.0
46 
 * @version $Id$
47 
 */
48 
public class ClassUtils {
49

    /**
51 
     * <p>The package separator character: <code>'&#x2e;' == {@value}</code>.</p>
52 
     */
53 
    public static final char PACKAGE_SEPARATOR_CHAR = '.';
54
55 
    /**
56 
     * <p>The package separator String: <code>"&#x2e;"</code>.</p>
57 
     */
58 
    public static final String PACKAGE_SEPARATOR = String.valueOf(PACKAGE_SEPARATOR_CHAR);

    /**

    /**
71 
     * Maps primitive <code>Class</code>es to their corresponding wrapper <code>Class</code>.
72 
     */
73 
    private static final Map<Class<?>, Class<?>> primitiveWrapperMap = new HashMap<Class<?>, Class<?>>();
74 
    static {
75 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Boolean.TYPE, Boolean.class);
76 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Byte.TYPE, Byte.class);
77 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Character.TYPE, Character.class);
78 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Short.TYPE, Short.class);
79 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Integer.TYPE, Integer.class);
80 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Long.TYPE, Long.class);
81 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Double.TYPE, Double.class);
82 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Float.TYPE, Float.class);
83 
         primitiveWrapperMap.put(Void.TYPE, Void.TYPE);
84 
    }
85
86 
    /**
87 
     * Maps wrapper <code>Class</code>es to their corresponding primitive types.
88 
     */
89 
    private static final Map<Class<?>, Class<?>> wrapperPrimitiveMap = new HashMap<Class<?>, Class<?>>();
90 
    static {
91 
        for (Class<?> primitiveClass : primitiveWrapperMap.keySet()) {
92 
            Class<?> wrapperClass = primitiveWrapperMap.get(primitiveClass);
93 
            if (!primitiveClass.equals(wrapperClass)) {
94 
                wrapperPrimitiveMap.put(wrapperClass, primitiveClass);
95 
            }
96 
        }
97 
    }

    /**
100 
     * Maps a primitive class name to its corresponding abbreviation used in array class names.
101 
     */
102 
    private static final Map<String, String> abbreviationMap = new HashMap<String, String>();
103
104 
    /**
105 
     * Maps an abbreviation used in array class names to corresponding primitive class name.
106 
     */
107 
    private static final Map<String, String> reverseAbbreviationMap = new HashMap<String, String>();
108
109 
    /**
110 
     * Add primitive type abbreviation to maps of abbreviations.
111 
     *
112 
     * @param primitive Canonical name of primitive type
113 
     * @param abbreviation Corresponding abbreviation of primitive type
114 
     */
115 
    private static void addAbbreviation(String primitive, String abbreviation) {
116 
        abbreviationMap.put(primitive, abbreviation);
117 
        reverseAbbreviationMap.put(abbreviation, primitive);
118 
    }
